{
  "video_id": "Jc9RdbHEFa0",
  "title": "Jared Ficklin: New ways to see music (with color! and fire!)",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Joseph Geni Reviewer: Morton Bast"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15709.0,
      "end_time": 16742.0,
      "text": "My passions"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 16742.0,
      "end_time": 20431.0,
      "text": "are music, technology and making things."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 20431.0,
      "end_time": 23614.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s the combination of these things"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 23614.0,
      "end_time": 26310.0,
      "text": "that has led me to the hobby of sound visualization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26310.0,
      "end_time": 30387.0,
      "text": "and, on occasion, has led me to play with fire."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 30388.0,
      "end_time": 32765.0,
      "text": "This is a Rubens&#39; tube. It&#39;s one of many I&#39;ve made over the years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 32765.0,
      "end_time": 34511.0,
      "text": "and I have one here tonight."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 34511.0,
      "end_time": 36360.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s about an 8-foot-long tube of metal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 36360.0,
      "end_time": 37371.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s got a hundred or so holes on top,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 37371.0,
      "end_time": 39124.0,
      "text": "on that side is the speaker, and here"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 39124.0,
      "end_time": 41300.0,
      "text": "is some lab tubing, and it&#39;s connected to this tank"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 41300.0,
      "end_time": 42900.0,
      "text": "of propane."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 44347.0,
      "end_time": 47716.0,
      "text": "So, let&#39;s fire it up and see what it does."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 53147.0,
      "end_time": 55380.0,
      "text": "So let&#39;s play a 550-herz frequency"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 55380.0,
      "end_time": 56553.0,
      "text": "and watch what happens."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 56602.0,
      "end_time": 65840.0,
      "text": "(Frequency)"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 65840.0,
      "end_time": 67797.0,
      "text": "Thank you. (Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 67798.0,
      "end_time": 69786.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s okay to applaud the laws of physics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 69786.0,
      "end_time": 71242.0,
      "text": "but essentially what&#39;s happening here"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 71242.0,
      "end_time": 73200.0,
      "text": "-- (Laughter) --"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 73200.0,
      "end_time": 77900.0,
      "text": "is the energy from the sound via the air and gas molecules"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 77100.0,
      "end_time": 79514.0,
      "text": "is influencing the combustion properties of propane,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 79514.0,
      "end_time": 81417.0,
      "text": "creating a visible waveform,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 81418.0,
      "end_time": 83738.0,
      "text": "and we can see the alternating regions of compression"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 83738.0,
      "end_time": 85778.0,
      "text": "and rarefaction that we call frequency,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 85778.0,
      "end_time": 87522.0,
      "text": "and the height is showing us amplitude."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 87522.0,
      "end_time": 89850.0,
      "text": "So let&#39;s change the frequency of the sound,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 89850.0,
      "end_time": 91274.0,
      "text": "and watch what happens to the fire."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 91275.0,
      "end_time": 101405.0,
      "text": "(Higher frequency)"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 101405.0,
      "end_time": 104755.0,
      "text": "So every time we hit a resonant frequency we get a standing wave"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 104755.0,
      "end_time": 106455.0,
      "text": "and that emergent sine curve of fire."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 106455.0,
      "end_time": 108330.0,
      "text": "So let&#39;s turn that off. We&#39;re indoors."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 108330.0,
      "end_time": 113624.0,
      "text": "Thank you. (Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 113624.0,
      "end_time": 115970.0,
      "text": "I also have with me a flame table."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 115971.0,
      "end_time": 117536.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s very similar to a Rubens&#39; tube, and it&#39;s also used"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 117536.0,
      "end_time": 119657.0,
      "text": "for visualizing the physical properties of sound,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 119657.0,
      "end_time": 121625.0,
      "text": "such as eigenmodes, so let&#39;s fire it up"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 121625.0,
      "end_time": 123875.0,
      "text": "and see what it does."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 127552.0,
      "end_time": 132200.0,
      "text": "Ooh. (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 132200.0,
      "end_time": 134994.0,
      "text": "Okay. Now, while the table comes up to pressure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 134994.0,
      "end_time": 136666.0,
      "text": "let me note here that the sound is not traveling"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 136666.0,
      "end_time": 139412.0,
      "text": "in perfect lines. It&#39;s actually traveling in all directions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 139412.0,
      "end_time": 142521.0,
      "text": "and the Rubens&#39; tube&#39;s a little like bisecting those waves"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 142521.0,
      "end_time": 144517.0,
      "text": "with a line, and the flame table&#39;s a little like"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 144517.0,
      "end_time": 146371.0,
      "text": "bisecting those waves with a plane,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 146371.0,
      "end_time": 150371.0,
      "text": "and it can show a little more subtle complexity, which is why"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 150371.0,
      "end_time": 152724.0,
      "text": "I like to use it to watch Geoff Farina play guitar."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 152724.0,
      "end_time": 195500.0,
      "text": "(Music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 195500.0,
      "end_time": 196769.0,
      "text": "All right, so it&#39;s a delicate dance."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 196770.0,
      "end_time": 199315.0,
      "text": "If you watch closely â€” (Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 199315.0,
      "end_time": 202820.0,
      "text": "If you watch closely, you may have seen"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 202820.0,
      "end_time": 204554.0,
      "text": "some of the eigenmodes, but also you may have seen"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 204554.0,
      "end_time": 209171.0,
      "text": "that jazz music is better with fire."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 209171.0,
      "end_time": 211180.0,
      "text": "Actually, a lot of things are better with fire in my world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 211181.0,
      "end_time": 213613.0,
      "text": "but the fire&#39;s just a foundation."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 213613.0,
      "end_time": 214761.0,
      "text": "It shows very well that eyes can hear,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 214761.0,
      "end_time": 216156.0,
      "text": "and this is interesting to me because"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 216156.0,
      "end_time": 219100.0,
      "text": "technology allows us to present sound to the eyes"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 219100.0,
      "end_time": 221873.0,
      "text": "in ways that accentuate the strength of the eyes"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 221873.0,
      "end_time": 224570.0,
      "text": "for seeing sound, such as the removal of time."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 224570.0,
      "end_time": 227953.0,
      "text": "So here, I&#39;m using a rendering algorithm to paint"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 227954.0,
      "end_time": 230417.0,
      "text": "the frequencies of the song \"Smells Like Teen Spirit\""
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 230417.0,
      "end_time": 232457.0,
      "text": "in a way that the eyes can take them in"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 232457.0,
      "end_time": 234701.0,
      "text": "as a single visual impression, and the technique"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 234701.0,
      "end_time": 236674.0,
      "text": "will also show the strengths of the visual cortex"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 236674.0,
      "end_time": 238290.0,
      "text": "for pattern recognition."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 238290.0,
      "end_time": 240168.0,
      "text": "So if I show you another song off this album,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 240169.0,
      "end_time": 243650.0,
      "text": "and another, your eyes will easily pick out"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 243650.0,
      "end_time": 246578.0,
      "text": "the use of repetition by the band Nirvana,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 246578.0,
      "end_time": 248435.0,
      "text": "and in the frequency distribution, the colors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 248435.0,
      "end_time": 251483.0,
      "text": "you can see the clean-dirty-clean sound"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 251483.0,
      "end_time": 252690.0,
      "text": "that they are famous for,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 252690.0,
      "end_time": 256690.0,
      "text": "and here is the entire album as a single visual impression,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 256690.0,
      "end_time": 258570.0,
      "text": "and I think this impression is pretty powerful."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 258570.0,
      "end_time": 260284.0,
      "text": "At least, it&#39;s powerful enough that"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 260284.0,
      "end_time": 261625.0,
      "text": "if I show you these four songs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 261625.0,
      "end_time": 264660.0,
      "text": "and I remind you that this is \"Smells Like Teen Spirit,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 264670.0,
      "end_time": 266386.0,
      "text": "you can probably correctly guess, without listening"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 266386.0,
      "end_time": 267820.0,
      "text": "to any music at all, that the song"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 267820.0,
      "end_time": 270114.0,
      "text": "a die hard Nirvana fan would enjoy is this song,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 270114.0,
      "end_time": 272369.0,
      "text": "\"I&#39;ll Stick Around\" by the Foo Fighters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 272370.0,
      "end_time": 274370.0,
      "text": "whose lead singer is Dave Grohl,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 274370.0,
      "end_time": 278148.0,
      "text": "who was the drummer in Nirvana."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 278148.0,
      "end_time": 279448.0,
      "text": "The songs are a little similar, but mostly"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 279448.0,
      "end_time": 281730.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m just interested in the idea that someday maybe"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 281740.0,
      "end_time": 285486.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ll buy a song because we like the way it looks."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 285486.0,
      "end_time": 286586.0,
      "text": "All right, now for some more sound data."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 286586.0,
      "end_time": 289238.0,
      "text": "This is data from a skate park,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 289238.0,
      "end_time": 291270.0,
      "text": "and this is Mabel Davis skate park"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 291270.0,
      "end_time": 293412.0,
      "text": "in Austin, Texas. (Skateboard sounds)"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 293412.0,
      "end_time": 294786.0,
      "text": "And the sounds you&#39;re hearing came from eight"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 294786.0,
      "end_time": 297200.0,
      "text": "microphones attached to obstacles around the park,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 297200.0,
      "end_time": 299186.0,
      "text": "and it sounds like chaos, but actually"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 299186.0,
      "end_time": 302532.0,
      "text": "all the tricks start with a very distinct slap,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 302533.0,
      "end_time": 304137.0,
      "text": "but successful tricks end with a pop,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 304137.0,
      "end_time": 305930.0,
      "text": "whereas unsuccessful tricks"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 305930.0,
      "end_time": 307786.0,
      "text": "more of a scratch and a tumble,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 307786.0,
      "end_time": 311796.0,
      "text": "and tricks on the rail will ring out like a gong, and"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 311796.0,
      "end_time": 314586.0,
      "text": "voices occupy very unique frequencies in the skate park."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 314586.0,
      "end_time": 316524.0,
      "text": "So if we were to render these sounds visually,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 316524.0,
      "end_time": 317931.0,
      "text": "we might end up with something like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 317931.0,
      "end_time": 320387.0,
      "text": "This is all 40 minutes of the recording,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 320387.0,
      "end_time": 322547.0,
      "text": "and right away the algorithm tells us"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 322547.0,
      "end_time": 324620.0,
      "text": "a lot more tricks are missed than are made,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 324620.0,
      "end_time": 326955.0,
      "text": "and also a trick on the rails is a lot more likely"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 326955.0,
      "end_time": 329827.0,
      "text": "to produce a cheer, and if you look really closely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 329827.0,
      "end_time": 331560.0,
      "text": "we can tease out traffic patterns."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 331560.0,
      "end_time": 337647.0,
      "text": "You see the skaters often trick in this direction. The obstacles are easier."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 337647.0,
      "end_time": 339352.0,
      "text": "And in the middle of the recording, the mics pick this up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 339352.0,
      "end_time": 342155.0,
      "text": "but later in the recording, this kid shows up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 342156.0,
      "end_time": 345840.0,
      "text": "and he starts using a line at the top of the park"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 345840.0,
      "end_time": 346886.0,
      "text": "to do some very advanced tricks on something"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 346886.0,
      "end_time": 347989.0,
      "text": "called the tall rail."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 347989.0,
      "end_time": 349861.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s fascinating. At this moment in time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 349861.0,
      "end_time": 353364.0,
      "text": "all the rest of the skaters turn their lines 90 degrees"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 353364.0,
      "end_time": 355142.0,
      "text": "to stay out of his way."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 355142.0,
      "end_time": 357685.0,
      "text": "You see, there&#39;s a subtle etiquette in the skate park,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 357685.0,
      "end_time": 359285.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s led by key influencers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 359285.0,
      "end_time": 362533.0,
      "text": "and they tend to be the kids who can do the best tricks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 362533.0,
      "end_time": 364963.0,
      "text": "or wear red pants, and on this day the mics picked that up."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 364963.0,
      "end_time": 368864.0,
      "text": "All right, from skate physics to theoretical physics."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 368864.0,
      "end_time": 370479.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m a big fan of Stephen Hawking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 370480.0,
      "end_time": 371816.0,
      "text": "and I wanted to use all eight hours"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 371816.0,
      "end_time": 374402.0,
      "text": "of his Cambridge lecture series to create an homage."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 374403.0,
      "end_time": 377467.0,
      "text": "Now, in this series he&#39;s speaking with the aid of a computer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 377467.0,
      "end_time": 380570.0,
      "text": "which actually makes identifying the ends of sentences"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 380571.0,
      "end_time": 383997.0,
      "text": "fairly easy. So I wrote a steering algorithm."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 383997.0,
      "end_time": 385957.0,
      "text": "It listens to the lecture, and then it uses"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 385957.0,
      "end_time": 388644.0,
      "text": "the amplitude of each word to move a point on the x-axis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 388644.0,
      "end_time": 391277.0,
      "text": "and it uses the inflection of sentences"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 391277.0,
      "end_time": 393431.0,
      "text": "to move a same point up and down on the y-axis."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 393431.0,
      "end_time": 396205.0,
      "text": "And these trend lines, you can see, there&#39;s more questions"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 396205.0,
      "end_time": 398750.0,
      "text": "than answers in the laws of physics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 398750.0,
      "end_time": 400108.0,
      "text": "and when we reach the end of a sentence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 400108.0,
      "end_time": 402443.0,
      "text": "we place a star at that location."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 402443.0,
      "end_time": 405243.0,
      "text": "So there&#39;s a lot of sentences, so a lot of stars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 405243.0,
      "end_time": 407599.0,
      "text": "and after rendering all of the audio, this is what we get."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 407599.0,
      "end_time": 410527.0,
      "text": "This is Stephen Hawking&#39;s universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 410528.0,
      "end_time": 417465.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 417465.0,
      "end_time": 419952.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s all eight hours of the Cambridge lecture series"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 419952.0,
      "end_time": 421800.0,
      "text": "taken in as a single visual impression,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 421800.0,
      "end_time": 423557.0,
      "text": "and I really like this image,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 423557.0,
      "end_time": 425365.0,
      "text": "but a lot of people think it&#39;s fake."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 425365.0,
      "end_time": 427709.0,
      "text": "So I made a more interactive version,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 427709.0,
      "end_time": 433165.0,
      "text": "and the way I did that is I used their position in time"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 433165.0,
      "end_time": 435532.0,
      "text": "in the lecture to place these stars into 3D space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 435532.0,
      "end_time": 437933.0,
      "text": "and with some custom software and a Kinect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 437933.0,
      "end_time": 440596.0,
      "text": "I can walk right into the lecture."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 440596.0,
      "end_time": 442396.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m going to wave through the Kinect here"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 442396.0,
      "end_time": 444228.0,
      "text": "and take control, and now I&#39;m going to reach out"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 444228.0,
      "end_time": 447467.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;m going to touch a star, and when I do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 447467.0,
      "end_time": 449411.0,
      "text": "it will play the sentence"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 449411.0,
      "end_time": 450876.0,
      "text": "that generated that star."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 450876.0,
      "end_time": 454691.0,
      "text": "Stephen Hawking: There is one, and only one, arrangement"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 454692.0,
      "end_time": 457491.0,
      "text": "in which the pieces make a complete picture."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 457491.0,
      "end_time": 461639.0,
      "text": "Jared Ficklin: Thank you. (Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 461639.0,
      "end_time": 464812.0,
      "text": "There are 1,400 stars."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 464812.0,
      "end_time": 466476.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a really fun way to explore the lecture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 466476.0,
      "end_time": 467943.0,
      "text": "and, I hope, a fitting homage."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 467943.0,
      "end_time": 473414.0,
      "text": "All right. Let me close with a work in progress."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 473415.0,
      "end_time": 476398.0,
      "text": "I think, after 30 years, the opportunity exists"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 476398.0,
      "end_time": 478502.0,
      "text": "to create an enhanced version of closed captioning."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 478502.0,
      "end_time": 480621.0,
      "text": "Now, we&#39;ve all seen a lot of TEDTalks online,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 480621.0,
      "end_time": 483548.0,
      "text": "so let&#39;s watch one now with the sound turned off"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 483548.0,
      "end_time": 487470.0,
      "text": "and the closed captioning turned on."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 487470.0,
      "end_time": 489616.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s no closed captioning for the TED theme song,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 489616.0,
      "end_time": 491729.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;re missing it, but if you&#39;ve watched enough of these,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 491729.0,
      "end_time": 493980.0,
      "text": "you hear it in your mind&#39;s ear,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 493980.0,
      "end_time": 496810.0,
      "text": "and then applause starts."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 496810.0,
      "end_time": 498271.0,
      "text": "It usually begins here, and it grows and then it falls."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 498271.0,
      "end_time": 500248.0,
      "text": "Sometimes you get a little star applause,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 500248.0,
      "end_time": 502734.0,
      "text": "and then I think even Bill Gates takes a nervous breath,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 502734.0,
      "end_time": 504424.0,
      "text": "and the talk begins."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 504424.0,
      "end_time": 510121.0,
      "text": "All right, so let&#39;s watch this clip again."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 510122.0,
      "end_time": 511378.0,
      "text": "This time, I&#39;m not going to talk at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 511378.0,
      "end_time": 512745.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s still going to be no audio,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 512745.0,
      "end_time": 514649.0,
      "text": "but what I am going to do is I&#39;m going to render the sound"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 514649.0,
      "end_time": 518965.0,
      "text": "visually in real time at the bottom of the screen."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 518965.00000000006,
      "end_time": 521756.00000000006,
      "text": "So watch closely and see what your eyes can hear."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 543140.0,
      "end_time": 545200.0,
      "text": "This is fairly amazing to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 545200.0,
      "end_time": 548353.0,
      "text": "Even on the first view, your eyes will successfully"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 548353.0,
      "end_time": 551440.0,
      "text": "pick out patterns, but on repeated views,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 551441.0,
      "end_time": 553130.0,
      "text": "your brain actually gets better"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 553130.0,
      "end_time": 554786.0,
      "text": "at turning these patterns into information."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 554786.0,
      "end_time": 556377.0,
      "text": "You can get the tone and the timbre"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 556377.0,
      "end_time": 557599.0,
      "text": "and the pace of the speech,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 557600.0,
      "end_time": 559664.0,
      "text": "things that you can&#39;t get out of closed captioning."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 559664.0,
      "end_time": 561848.0,
      "text": "That famous scene in horror movies"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 561848.0,
      "end_time": 564496.0,
      "text": "where someone is walking up from behind"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 564496.0,
      "end_time": 566456.0,
      "text": "is something you can see,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 566456.0,
      "end_time": 569160.0,
      "text": "and I believe this information would be something"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 569160.0,
      "end_time": 571963.0,
      "text": "that is useful at times when the audio is turned off"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 571963.0,
      "end_time": 574904.0,
      "text": "or not heard at all, and I speculate that deaf audiences"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 574904.0,
      "end_time": 576810.0,
      "text": "might actually even be better"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 576810.0,
      "end_time": 577862.0,
      "text": "at seeing sound than hearing audiences."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 577862.0,
      "end_time": 579360.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know. It&#39;s a theory right now."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 579360.0,
      "end_time": 580881.0,
      "text": "Actually, it&#39;s all just an idea."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 580881.0,
      "end_time": 585720.0,
      "text": "And let me end by saying that sound moves in all directions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 585720.0,
      "end_time": 587490.0,
      "text": "and so do ideas."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 587490.0,
      "end_time": 590161.0,
      "text": "Thank you. (Applause)"
    }
  ]
}